After this we looked at describing common gateway interface methods which are GET and POST. GET essentially gets its input from an environmental variable such as a http request which then goes to the web server. POST gets the input from a standard input and then uses this to send data via http to the web server. These are the more common gateway interface methods however there are others such as PUT, DELETE and PATCH. \
